==English==

===Etymology===
From ecclesiastical Latin [[Pharao]], from Greek [[Φαραώ]], from Hebrew [[פַּרְעֹה]] (par‘ōh), from Egyptian [[pr-aA]] (per-aa) ‘great house’, from [[pr]] ‘dwelling-place, temple, house’ + the verb [[aA]] ‘great, spectacular’.  Final H comes directly from the Hebrew.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈfɛ:rəʊ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The supreme ruler of [[Ancient Egypt]]; a formal address for the sovereign seat of power as personified by the 'king' in an institutional role of Horus son of Osiris; often used by metonymy for Ancient Egyptian sovereignty

===Derived terms===
*adjective [[pharaonic]]

